pageContext.claim: “James Woods. I don't know James, but he's an interesting guy and he's a conservative guy and he's a straight shooter. He's tough. But then when they want to take him off and other people like him, many in this room, some in this room, it's a very, very bad -- it's a very bad thing.”
pageContext.analysis: Twitter technically did not ban Woods. He could regain access if he removes a tweet that broke the platform's rules. Woods, a pro-Trump actor, tweeted "hang them all" after special counsel Robert Mueller's report was released.
